PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1782389904
OL,3,CMother of dying toddler delayed 999
OL,4,Ccall, murder trial hears
OL,6,F"It would have been, we will invite
OL,7,Fyou to conclude, perfectly obvious
OL,8,Fthat child was being seriously
OL,9,Fassaulted on a regular basis.
OL,11,F"The failure to take her to hospital
OL,12,Ffor days after her leg had been broken
OL,13,Fand the significant delay in calling
OL,14,F999 on the 13th is evidence of the
OL,15,Ffact that both were responsible for
OL,16,Fand aware of a series of violent
OL,17,Fassaults that they wanted to keep away
OL,18,Ffrom medical scrutiny if at all
OL,19,Fpossible."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOU{D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G9/11
